I haven't been active on here lately and that's mainly because the dogs and I have been going through training and I just wanted to focus on them during it.

During the test, I was so nervous that Lexi was going to pick up on my anxiety and react but she thankfully pulled through with only one hiccup. 

For our sit and lay down/stay in place, you can see in the video I had trouble getting Lexi to focus on me and listen to what I'm saying. I was extremely frustrated cause I know she can do it but I had to remind myself that being frustrated wasn't going to help her. So I had to readjust and after the second try, she did it.

I'm super excited to see what's in store for us next. Our trainer recommends we try Rally, Scent work, and Temperament test so I might sign her up for one of those.
